The National Working Committee (NWC) of the PDP has approved the nomination of former Kogi State governor, Idris Wada, as the chairman of the committee to screen all aspirants for the upcoming Anambra State Governorship Election. To serve with him on the committee as members are Sen. Ehigie Uzamere, Mrs Martha Bodunrin, Rt. Hon. Jones Onyereri, and Chief James Ugwu who is the secretary. A statement issued by Col. Austin Akobundu (rtd), PDP National Organizing Secretary on Saturday informed that the screening exercise is scheduled for April 12 – 13, 2021 at the national secretariat of the party. “It is expected that the aspirants will exercise exemplary conduct and strict adherence to rules and regulations during the assessment that will justify the confidence reposed in them by the leadership of our party,” the statement said. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state…Ex-governor Wada heads  Ex-governor Wada heads Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report…Ex-governor Wada heads  Ex-governor Wada heads SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that
